      • possiblyEqualsCondition1

        public boolean possiblyEqualsCondition1(Song song)
        Parameters:
        song - song
        Returns:
        boolean This is one of the two conditions that two songs are possibly equal. Two songs have the same name and either artist or album is the same. It returns true if two songs meet this condition, otherwise returns false.

      • possiblyEqualsCondition2

        public boolean possiblyEqualsCondition2(Song song)
        Parameters:
        song - song
        Returns:
        boolean This is one of the two conditions that two songs are possibly equal. Two songs have the same artist and album, and the names are the same if converted to lower case and punctuation is ignored. It returns true if two songs meet this condition, otherwise returns false.

      • setArtistForSong

        public boolean setArtistForSong(Library library)
        Parameters:
        library - the music library
        Returns:
        boolean This finds the artist for a piece of song and set relation on the artist and song if there is such artist in the library or AudioD when user want to import a piece of song. It returns true if the artist is linked to the song, return false otherwise.

      • setAlbumForSong

        public boolean setAlbumForSong(Library library)
        Parameters:
        library - the music library
        Returns:
        boolean This finds album for a piece of song and set relation on the album and song if there is such album in the library or AudioDB when user want to import a piece of song. Since the album searching process from AudioDB is based on the artist, when there is no such artist in AudioDB the album searching process will not be conducted. It returns true if the album is linked to the song, otherwise returns false.
